Bulgarian manager Dimitar Penev announced his 22-man  World Cup squad here on Monday:
Goalkeepers: Borislav Mikhailov, Nikolov
Defenders: Emil Kremenliev, Tsanko Tsvetanov, Trifon Ivanov, Petar  Houbtchev, Nikolai Iliev
Midfielders: Ilian Kiriakov, Zlatko Yankov, Yordan Letchkov, Ivailo  Yordanov, Petar Mikhtarski, Georgi Georguiev, Ivailo Andonov
Forwards: Emil Kostadinov, Hristo Stoichkov, Krassimir Balakov, Nasko  Sirakov, Bontcho Gentchev, Petar Alexandrov, Daniel Borimirov, Velko Yotov
